The paper proposes a tool and technique for code recommendation, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The technique involves indexing a large code corpus and searching for structural similarities, which suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions implementing the tool for 4 different programming languages, which suggests programming languages (cs.PL) as a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses clustering and intersecting search results, which suggests natural language processing (cs.CL) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the study conducted with 12 programmers suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as a potential sub-category.
